  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse by making partial restitution. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the sentencing guidelines for a non-violent, first-time offense of this magnitude generally lean toward shorter periods of incarceration or alternative sentencing. A 10-year demand from a spectator is wildly disproportionate to the scale of the crime and legal standards. Taking into account the need for deterrence and the defendant's clean record, a period of 6 months serves as a punitive measure while allowing for rehabilitation.",
  "verdict": 6
}
